{"to":["sarah.thompson@techinnovations.com"],"subject":"Requested Application Materials – John Doe","body":"Hi Sarah,

Thank you for your message. Please find my updated application materials below:

1. Updated résumé
   • PDF/online view: https://www.notion.so/John-Doe-Updated-Resume-20f0dc8fa0db81598d09c8684c32f177  
   (You can click “•••” → “Export” to download a PDF copy if that is more convenient.)

2. Professional references
   • Jane Smith – Engineering Manager, Google – jane.smith@google.com  
   • Mike Johnson – Senior Developer, Meta – mike.johnson@fb.com  
   • Emily Davis – Team Lead, Apple – emily.davis@apple.com  
   (Phone numbers are available upon request.)

3. Supporting documents
   • Certifications: AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, Certified Scrum Master (digital badges and PDFs available on request).  
   • Key projects: A concise summary is included in the résumé; a longer narrative with links, screenshots, and code samples is here: <https://www.notion.so/Personal-Workspace-1f00dc8fa0db809ea302d103fbfc769d#Projects>

If you need the files in a different format or any additional information, please let me know and I will be happy to provide it right away.

Thank you for your consideration.

Best regards,
John Doe
john.doe@gmail.com
(+1) 555-555-0123"}

formatted_items.content:
Thought process:

1. Identified Sarah’s request for three items: résumé, professional references, supporting documents.
2. Queried Notion for “resume” → located page “John Doe Updated Resume”; opened to confirm content and Notion share-link.
3. Queried Notion for “references” → located page “Professional References”; opened and extracted three reference contacts.
4. Searched Notion for portfolio / project summaries / certifications. Found certifications section inside existing résumé page and a Personal Workspace page with a Projects block; chose that as the most relevant project summary link.
5. Quick Gmail search for existing attached résumé PDFs returned none; decided to supply Notion links (allows online viewing & exporting to PDF) rather than create new attachments, simplifying delivery.
6. Composed concise, courteous email:
   • Thanked Sarah.  
   • Provided direct Notion link to résumé with instructions to export PDF.  
   • Listed references with names, roles, and emails.  
   • Addressed supporting docs: certifications and longer project narrative link; offered PDFs/badges if required.  
   • Offered further assistance and provided contact info.  
7. Sent the email via gmail_send_message.
